{"article_id":"IEcfwpCtlSrTDS27","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"But the weight of history is against them .","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"The fight has never been won at the ballot box .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"In states","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"where same-sex marriage is legal now","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"- Connecticut , Iowa , Massachusetts , New Hampshire , New York and Vermont , as well as in the District of Columbia -","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"it has been made possible through court rulings or legislative action .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"In the 32 states ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"including California ,","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"in which voters have had a say ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"they have rejected it .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"In November , voters in four states will weigh in on same-sex marriage .","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"There is a chance","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"that in three it could become law ;","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"besides the initiative in Maine , voters in Maryland and Washington State will decide","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"whether to repeal same-sex marriage laws","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"recently passed in those states .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"In the fourth , Minnesota , voters will consider whether to amend the state Constitution","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"to ban it .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"The loss in Maine in 2009 was a heartbreak for the movement .","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"The Legislature had legalized it","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"and the governor , John Baldacci , a Democrat , had signed it into law .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"But opponents forced it to a referendum ,","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"and the public voted to repeal it , 53 to 47 percent , a difference of about 30,000 votes .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"That was a surprise","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"because polls at the time indicated","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"that a majority of voters would approve it .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"And therein lies the hope of the opposition here this year ;","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"while state and national polls suggest","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"that a majority supports same-sex marriage ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"voters have not always told pollsters the truth .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"\" I ' ll be surprised","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"if we don ' t win , \"","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"said Carroll Conley Jr. , executive director of the Christian Civic League of Maine and a board member of Protect Marriage Maine , a group","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"leading the opposition .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"\" When it ' s framed as ' Should people be able to marry","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"regardless of sexual orientation ? '","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"you see a significant change from five years ago , \"","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"\" But","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"if you ask ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"' Should marriage be defined as one man , one women ? '","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"we don ' t see significant changes . \"","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"The proposed wording of the ballot question here is , \" Do you want to allow same-sex couples to marry ? \"","depth":4},{"id":43,"text":"But proponents want it to point out","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"that neither clergy nor religious institutions would have to perform or host a marriage against their beliefs , a clause","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"that could ease some fears .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"A decision on the wording is due from Maine ' s secretary of state by the end of July .","depth":3},{"id":47,"text":"Newsletter Sign Up","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"Continue reading the main story","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"Please verify","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"you 're not a robot","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"by clicking the box .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Invalid email address .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Please re-enter .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"You must select a newsletter","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"to subscribe to .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":57,"text":"You will receive emails","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"containing news content , updates and promotions from The New York Times .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"You may opt-out at any time .","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"You agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for The New York Times 's products and services .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"Thank you for subscribing .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"An error has occurred .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"Please try again later .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"View all New York Times newsletters .","depth":3},{"id":65,"text":"Mr. Conley said","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"he doubted","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"voters would approve same-sex marriage ,","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"in part because people resist change .","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"\" From a purely political perspective , a ' no ' is easier than a ' yes ' on any referendum. \"","depth":5},{"id":70,"text":"he said .","depth":5},{"id":71,"text":"Some money for the opposition campaign is coming from collection plates","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"passed at churches .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"But most is expected to come from the National Organization for Marriage ,","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"which funneled almost $ 2 million into Maine","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"to help defeat the measure in 2009 .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"One complication for the opposition this year is that the Roman Catholic Church plans to be less active","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"than it was in 2009 ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"when church officials were criticized for being too involved .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"Mr. Conley acknowledged","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"that the campaign in support of same-sex marriage appeared highly organized and well financed .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"Advocates expect to raise about $ 5 million ,","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"while opponents expect less than half as much .","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"Matt McTighe , campaign manager for Mainers United for Marriage , a coalition of groups","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"advocating gay marriage ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"his side had more time","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"to make its case this year","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"and was playing offense , not defense .","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"\" Normally , when marriage comes up on the ballot ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"it ' s in response to a court case or legislative action","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"and at most","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"- as in 2009 here and in Maryland and Washington -","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"you have six months to really go out","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"and defend whatever that court or legislature did , \"","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"Mr. McTighe said .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"\" Maine is the first state","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"to proactively bring this initiative to voters ,","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"and that ' s allowed us to control our own fate . \"","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"The campaign ' s centerpiece is a canvassing effort","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"aimed at undecided voters .","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"Mr. McTighe said","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"a personal approach was the most effective way","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"to convey the message .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"The coalition has conducted 100,000 \" conversations \" in two years ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"with perhaps one in every five people open to changing his or her views .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"Amelia Nugent , 23 ,","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"who was canvassing last week on a warm , buggy night in Falmouth ,","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"said","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"she usually told people","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"that she wanted to have the same kind of loving and committed marriage","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"that they had .","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"\" It ' s just humanizing the issue , \"","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"she said","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"as she walked door to door .","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"\" It ' s about love and family . \"","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"Sometimes people are rude ,","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"she said ,","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"asking her","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"if she wants to marry their dog .","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"Others will talk for 45 minutes ,","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"and leave her feeling","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"she has made progress .","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"The other night , a few people turned Ms. Nugent away ;","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"most","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"who talked to her","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"said","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"they already supported gay marriage .","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"\" It ' s such a nonissue , \"","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"said Judith Coye , 52 , a banker ,","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"who spoke briefly with Ms. Nugent .","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"George Bloom , 57 , an environmental engineer","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"who was watering his garden ,","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"said","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"he saw no problem with it .","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"He said","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"that he had had gay friends over the years","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"and that allowing them to marry \" just seems fair . \"","depth":13}],"relations":[{"parent":277,"left":185,"right":276,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":185,"left":180,"right":184,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":156,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":148,"rig